<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 29 at 10:07AM CDT  by NWS Springfield</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Hickory
and northwestern Polk Counties through 1045 AM CDT...
At 1007 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Humansville, or 13 miles northeast of Stockton, moving northeast at
45 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Pomme de Terre Lake...            Pomme De Terre State Park...
Pittsburg...                      Humansville...
Hermitage...                      Wheatland...
Flemington...                     Nemo...
Elkton...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
